{"questionId":"9069308","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Magnesium is a reactive metal often found in alloys.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Magnesium is sometimes used as a sacrificial anode to protect steel from corrosion.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate the free energy change, Δ<em>G</em><sup>⦵</sup>, in kJ, of the cell reaction. Use sections 1 and 2 of the data booklet.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«Δ<em>G</em>º = -nFEº»<br>n = 2<br><em><strong>OR</strong></em><br>Δ<em>G</em>º = «-»2×96500×1.92 / «-»370,560 «J» ✔</p>\n<p>-371 «kJ» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>For n = 1, award [1] for –185 «kJ».</em></p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[1 max]</strong> for (+)371 «kJ»</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069308","referenceCode":"22M.2.hl.TZ1.b(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"Calculate the free energy change, ΔG⦵, in kJ, of the cell reaction. Use sections 1 and 2 of the data booklet.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes","19.1 Electrochemical cells","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 19: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}